This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper presents a deep learning driven automated theorem prover for higher-order logic, which suggests that it belongs to the Machine Learning category.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper's focus on developing an automated theorem prover using deep reinforcement learning techniques falls under the scope of Artificial Intelligence.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper's main contribution is in the area of automated theorem proving for higher-order logic, which is a subfield of Logic in Computer Science.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper's use of the HOL Light theorem prover as a framework for developing an environment for machine learning of higher-order theorem proving suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages category.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper's development of an open-source framework for machine learning of higher-order theorem proving using HOL Light may also fall under the scope of Software Engineering.
